{{Class 5|hexagon=✦|color-h=32|color-s=71%|color-l=61%|class=1|safety=Safe|security=Secure|entity=Minorly Hostile Entities}}

Level 235, is the 236<sup>th</sup> level of the backrooms, although what most of it once was is now regarded as [[Level 499]]

{{Borderimage|image=Tiuoya1xiwr91.jpg|align=center|width=350px|caption=An image of current Level 235|id=1}}

<span style="font-family:Snowburst One; font-size:40px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2a0ee, #f59847); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #FFFFFF 0px 0px 4px; color:#f59847">Description.</span>

Level 235 resembles a set of bowling alleys and recreational grounds, with arcades and playrooms settled inbetween. Cylindrical tables along with rectangular ones may also constantly appear within Level 235, these tables mostly inhibit white-breaded sandwiches with sliced mature cheddar and tomato wedged between them; alongside a drink contained within a plastic cup of either Coca-cola or Pepsi. Consuming these items leads to a feeling of fufillment within the wanderer, replenishing their sanity and making them feel more jubilant than usual.

The lighting of Level 235 remains functional in some areas, while other areas remain in complete darknesss due to their lack of electricity. The reasoning for this appears to be a lack of electrical generators in Level 235, due to the slowly decreasing size of the level; along with the current state of the level causing issues with the remaining [[Object 70|Ferronix Silicate]] batteries. A few areas have lighting that often flickers, the flickering having varying intervals ranging from one second to approximately thirty-two seconds between states. An interesting thing to note is that any individuals with Photosensitive Epiliepsy do not experience seisures when viewing the flashing lights.

{{Borderimage|image=235-2.webp|align=center|width=350px|caption=A golfing area within Level 235|id=2}}

The bowling alleys within Level 235 exhibit multiple strange properties, one of such is that landing a strike or gutter causes the wanderer to achieve an exorbant amont of positive or negative points; with numbers exceeding the sextillions. Other properties include the lane twisting in a zig zag pattern, the pins suddenly inverting colors and the lane refusing to restock the pins permenantly. The golf courses within Level 235 exhibit similar properties, such as the goal areas suddenly tranforming into bottomless holes that lead to other areas of the level, lighting issues, and multiple instances of [[Phenomenon 11]].

{{Borderimage|image=235-3.jpg|align=center|width=350px|caption=An area in Level 235 with stable lighting|id=3}}

The arcade machines within Level 235 appear unconnected to any electricity source, therefore remaining disfunctional permenantly. Any attempts to turn on or supply electricity to these machines has failed; and in worse scenarios has caused the machine to explode entirely. The only function the arcade machines possess is spewing out tickets at a high rate, even though they aren't hooked up to any electrical components; along with any external lighting flickering in a similar fashion. Rarely the arcade machines will turn on for a set amount of time before suddenly switching off, the games featured on these machines are usually future releases within the frontrooms; although the game controls are wonkier than usual. Once these machines turn off they will no longer switch on again, even if another occurence targets the machine in question.

Infobooths and other kiosks can also be found within Level 235, these kiosks usually contain leaflets or other forms of print-publishing related to Level 235. The media within these leaflets usually displays information and areas of interest within the level, such as the Wacky Bowling Course and the Antaria Derby. Other media usually includes issues from Backrooms Today regarding other levels or small pieces of literature made by BackBorn authors. The material these prints are made out of appears to be indestructable, with any attempt to rip apart the prints leading to no visible tearing whatsoever. What material makes up these prints is currently unknown, however a theory suggests that the prints may be constructed of a highly durable object.

<span style="font-family:Snowburst One; font-size:40px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2a0ee, #f59847); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #FFFFFF 0px 0px 4px; color:#f59847">Additional Notes.</span>

*Most of the level is scattered into moderately sized or large clusters that reside within or outside of [[Level 499]]'s spatial location, with the level's size slowly decreasing as [[Architect Industries]] continue to expand [[Level 499]] into the larger areas of Level 235. 

*Any mentions of Level 235 inside of online spaces immediately go under heavy censoring similarly to [[Level 72]] due to the fears of [[Architect Industries]] discovering more areas of the level, causing its size to decrease more.

*All previous entrances that used to lead into Level 235 have been directed to lead into other levels via [[Object 55|Permenant Interlevel Hyperlinks]] placed by the [[A.A.E.G.]], an example being an entrance from [[Level 107]] now leading into [[Level 169]].

<span style="font-family:Snowburst One; font-size:40px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2a0ee, #f59847); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #FFFFFF 0px 0px 4px; color:#f59847">Groups and Colonies.</span>

Although suitable for habitation, Level 235 doesn't contain any groups or colonies. Mainly due to the level's slowly shrinking size and competition between groups over the level's resources.

<span style="font-family:Snowburst One; font-size:40px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2a0ee, #f59847); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #FFFFFF 0px 0px 4px; color:#f59847">Entities.</span>

Level 235's entities usually reside within the more lit up areas within the level, such entities include: [[Entity 17|Kats]], [[Entity 69|Lightlurkers]], [[Entity 28|Trotting Snails]] and rarely, [[Entity 33|Reticents]]

<span style="font-family:Snowburst One; font-size:40px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2a0ee, #f59847); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #FFFFFF 0px 0px 4px; color:#f59847">Entrances and Exits.</span>
===<span style="font-family:Snowburst One; font-size:30px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2a0ee, #f59847); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #FFFFFF 0px 0px 4px; color:#f59847">Entrances.</span>===
*Entering a bowling alley located somewhere in [[Level 79|Strums of Suburbia]] can lead into Level 235.
*[[Level 120|Chokepoint]] is theorised to have an entrance to Level 235 located within its lower areas.
*[[Level 25|Out of Order]] has a chance of leading into Level 235 if an individual walks far enough.
*A rather sketchy elevator in [[Level 68|Think About The Water Bills]] leads into Level 235.
===<span style="font-family:Snowburst One; font-size:30px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #f2a0ee, #f59847); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; text-shadow: #FFFFFF 0px 0px 4px; color:#f59847">Exits.</span>===
*A few areas of Level 235 can exit into [[Level 40|The Video Rental Store]].
*Interacting with a distablised sandwich teleports the wanderer to [[Level 213|Imaginative Dullness]].
*Going through a metal door may lead into [[Level 31|The Roller Rink]]
